    intro i
    simp [deriv_nth_partial, mul_comm]
    <;> field_simp [deriv_sub, deriv_mul, deriv_id'', mul_comm]
    <;> ring
```

This shows that the derivative of `nth_partial i f ((1 - t) • x + t • y)` with respect to `t` is `nth_partial i f ((1 - t) • x + t • y) * (y - x)`. This is derived using the chain rule: the derivative of `f(g(t))` is `f'(g(t)) * g'(t)`. Here, `g(t) = (1 - t) • x + t • y`, and `g'(t) = y - x`.

Now we can combine these results to prove the main theorem:

```tactics
  rw [h1]
  funext t
  simp [h2]
  <;> ring_nf
